subtitleNullable: Retail sales are sales made in physical stores using a (POS) system.
descriptionNullable:
In the simplest terms, retail and e-commerce seem to be very similar: retail and e-commerce both refer to what happens when a product from a business is sold to an individual consumer for their own use, except one of them is done exclusively through the Internet.

This table contains 3 series, with data for years 2016 - 2017 (not all combinations necessarily have data for all years). This table contains data described by the following dimensions (Not all combinations are available): Geography (1 item: Canada); Sales (3 items: Retail trade; Electronic shopping and mail-order houses; Retail E-commerce sales).

Of course there is a **MetaData** that describes lots of information about the main dataset values.
This dataset helps you to find out how a retail e-commerce can work.
So go for it and create some interesting notebook about it.
Feel free to ask me anything about this dataset on discussion section.
Good luck
